SIMPLE: respite
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Respite
<hw>Res"pite</hw> <pr>(r?s"p?t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>respit</ets>, F. <ets>r⟦eacute⟧pit</ets>, from L.
<ets>respectus</ets> respect, regard, delay, in LL., the deferring of a
day. See <er>Respect</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A putting off of that
which was appointed; a postponement or delay.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I crave but four day's <qex>respite</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Temporary intermission of labor, or of any process
or operation; interval of rest; pause; delay.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Without more
<xex>respite</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Some pause and <qex>respite</qex> only I require.</q>
<rj><qau>Denham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Temporary suspension
of the execution of a capital offender; reprieve.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>The delay of appearance at court granted to a jury beyond the
proper term.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Pause; interval; stop; cessation; delay;
postponement; stay; reprieve.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Respite</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Respite
<hw>Res"pite</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Respited</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Respiting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OF. <ets>respiter</ets>, LL.
<ets>respectare</ets>. See <er>Respite</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety>
<def>To give or grant a respite to.</def> Specifically: <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>To delay or postpone; to put off.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>To keep
back from execution; to reprieve.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Forty days longer we do <qex>respite</qex> you.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(c)</sd> <def>To relieve by a pause or interval of rest.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧To <xex>respite</xex> his day labor with repast.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Respiteless</ent>⟦br⟧
